From: ASUS ProArt PX13 debug <snd-repair@local>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] ASoC: tas2783: honor dai_link channel map for SDW port

snd_sdw_params_to_config() documents that drivers may override fields in
port_config. For multicodec links, asoc_sdw_hw_params() fills per-codec
ch_maps; apply ch_map->ch_mask when calling sdw_stream_add_slave() instead
of always programming the full PCM channel count on every slave.

Reported-on: AMD ACP70 2x TAS2783 (stereo playback validated with
speaker-test per channel).

Signed-off-by: ASUS ProArt PX13 debug <snd-repair@local>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/tas2783-sdw.c | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/codecs/tas2783-sdw.c b/sound/soc/codecs/tas2783-sdw.c
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/tas2783-sdw.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/tas2783-sdw.c
@@ -943,6 +943,21 @@ static s32 tas_sdw_hw_params(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream,
 	else
 		port_config.num = 2;
 
+	{
+		struct snd_soc_pcm_runtime *rtd =
+			snd_soc_substream_to_rtd(substream);
+		const struct snd_soc_dai_link_ch_map *ch_map;
+		int i;
+
+		for_each_rtd_ch_maps(rtd, i, ch_map) {
+			if (snd_soc_rtd_to_codec(rtd, ch_map->codec) == dai &&
+			    ch_map->ch_mask) {
+				port_config.ch_mask = ch_map->ch_mask;
+				break;
+			}
+		}
+	}
+
 	ret = sdw_stream_add_slave(sdw_peripheral,
 				   &stream_config, &port_config, 1, sdw_stream);
 	if (ret)
